Products.description: The Kobe Bryant 1996 Metal Rookie pictures a young 'Black Mamba' at his introductory Laker press conference. In the 1996 NBA Draft, Kobe was selected 13th overall by the Charlotte Hornets straight out of Lower Merion High School in Philadelphia but was subsequently traded to the Los Angeles Lakers on draft night. For the next two decades, Kobe played the game of basketball with unmatched intensity and dedication, winning five championships and one NBA MVP award among many other accolades, becoming a cultural icon. Playing alongside Shaquille O'Neal and Paul Gasol at different points of his career, while echoeing the playing style of Michael Jordan, Kobe created an everlasting legacy for himself on the court. Off the court, Kobe was a global ambassador for the sport, successful in business as an investor, and he even won an Oscar for one of his many creative masterpieces post-retirement.

Products.description: The Jayson Tatum 2017 Prizm Silver Rookie is the most popular prizm rookie parallel to own of the talented former Duke standout. The silver prizm is king when it comes to unnumbered Prizm parallels and it should continue to grow in value. The Boston Celtics swapped picks with the Philadelphia 76ers and selected Tatum with the #3 overall pick in the 2017 NBA Draft ahead of De'Aaron Fox, Donovan Mitchell, Bam Adebayo, and John Collins. The young Celtic has an opportunity to be the leader of this draft class given his refined offensive talent and two-way upside. Following the initial release of Prizm Basketball in 2012, the base Prizm rookie has taken over as the main card to own of any young player and it should continue to cement its place within the market.
